Suetonius (Caesar, c. 38) speaks of Caesar’s ‘ congiaria.' He paid his old soldiers well, and he gave the people something too. A modern usurper need not care for the people, but he must please his soldiers. Caesar feasted the people, and he distributed meat among them.
